def: Not stratified; -- applied to massive rocks, as granite,porphyry, etc., and also to deposits of loose material, as theglacial till, which occur in masses without layers or strata.
from Solder, v. t. Soldering iron, Soldering tool, aninstrument for soldering, consisting of a bit or bolt of copperhaving a pointed or wedge-shaped end, and furnished with a handle.
To take into, or as into, the stomach or alimentary canal. SirT. Browne.
The quality or state of being tortile, twisted, or wreathed.
Pertaining to, or characterized by, alliteration; as,alliterative poetry.-- Al*lit"er*a*tive*ly, adv.-- Al*lit"er*a*tive*ness, n.
To fill with artifice and duplicity; to complicate; toembarrass. [Obs.]How doth it [sin] perplex and intrique the whole course of yourlives! Dr. J. Scott.
Not worldly; spiritual; holy. Hawthorne.-- Un*world"li*ness, n.
The act of inclosing in a capsule; the growth of a membranearound (any part) so as to inclose it in a capsule.
Being above ground. "Superterranean quarries." Mrs. Trollope.
Belonging to, or resembling, a family, or order, of plants ofwhich the cashew tree is the type, and the species of sumac are wellknown examples.
People; a nation; a man. [Obs.] Piers Plowman. Bp. Gibson.
A form of hydrometer, specially graduated, for finding thedensity of milk, and thus discovering whether it has been mixed withwater or some of the cream has been removed.
